==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anglo-Norman
<hw>Anglo-Norman</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the
English and Normans, or to the Normans who settled in England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anglo-Norman</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Anglo-Norman
<hw>Anglo-Norman</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of the English
Normans, or the Normans who conquered England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the French (Norman) language used in medieval
England.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Anglo-French</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>anglophile</ent>⟦br⟧
